The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 French consultancy firm Seureca, engaged by the state government in 2004 to look into the functioning of some civic bodies, submitted its final report on Salt Lake to the chairman of the townships municipality, Biswajiban Majumdar, on Tuesday. According to the report, upgrade of the Bidhannagar Municipalitys services would cost about Rs 86 crore. The report focusses on sewage, drainage, conservancy and water supply. 

 he state urban development department, Calcutta Metropolitan Development Authority (CMDA) and the Bidhannagar Municipality will go through the six volume report. The CMDA will then seek funds for the implementation of the reports suggestions under Jawaharlal Nehru National Urban Renewal Mission. Seureca had submitted an interim report on September 26. Municipal affairs minister Asok Bhattacharya had requested it to submit the final report. 

 Legal aid research and resource centres will be set up in all 53 jails across the state to provide assistance to convicts, Union minister of state for law K.Ventakatapathy said on Tuesday. He made the announcement while inaugurating a daylong workshop on legal aid for prisoners at Presidency jail. State minister for jails Biswanath Chowdhury and law minister Rabilal Mitra were present. 

 A 45-year-old man was run over by an unidentified vehicle on JL Nehru Road around 12.45 pm on Tuesday. He was taken to Sambhunath Pandit Hospital, where he was pronounced dead. Police are looking for the vehicle.

 A 38-year-old man was critically injured after being run over by a truck on Ramnagar Road, in the port area, early on Tuesday. The man was taken to SSKM Hospital, where his condition was stated to be critical. The driver was arrested and the vehicle impounded, said an officer of Garden Reach police station.

 Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee on Tuesday inaugurated a bio-pharmaceutical plant at Harinavi Chowhati, in Sonarpur, on the southern fringes of the city. He stressed the need to improve work ethics and the understanding between the management and workers. Left Front chairman Biman Bose and health minister Surjya Kanta Mishra were present.

 IIT Khargapur and Indian Statistical Institute are organising an international workshop on Research Issues in Digital Library at Vedic Village from December 12-15. State IT minister Debesh Das will chair the technical session of the workshop.

 As part of the Vijay Diwas celebrations, the eastern command headquarters of the army will organise a military tattoo programme, including skydiving and dog show, on December 13 and 14 at the Fort William stadium.

 The All India Conference of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists (AICOG) will be held in Calcutta from January 5 to 9. Bengal Obstetrics and Gynaecological Society is organising the workshop. Geeta Ganguly Mukherjee, chairperson of AICOG, said womens health and empowerment would be the key issue. More than 7,000 delegates from across the country and around 100 from abroad will take part in the conference. 

 Bhola Adok, 40, and Pradip Shaw, 35, were run over by a truck on Diamond Harbour Road, near Bishnupur, on Tuesday morning. Police said the two were taken to a local hospital, where they were pronounced dead.

